---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Call for Participation: From Dead-Ends to Dialogue (DIS '25 Workshop)" 
  description="Announcing the Third Workshop on GenAI & Design Research at DIS 2025. Share your experiences overcoming semantic and practical stopsigns."
  ogImage="/square-workshop.png"
>
  <section class="mt-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6">
    <h1 class="font-bold text-3xl mb-4">Call for Participation: From Dead-Ends to Dialogue (DIS '25 Workshop)</h1>
    <p class="opacity-60 mb-6">
      Announcing the Third Workshop on GenAI & Design Research at DIS 2025. Share your experiences overcoming semantic and practical stopsigns.
    </p>
    
    <div class="flex gap-4 mb-6">
      <img 
        src="/willem-logo.webp" 
        alt="Willem van der Maden" 
        class="w-[40px] aspect-square object-cover rounded-full" 
        width="40" 
        height="40" 
        loading="lazy" 
        decoding="async"
      />
      <div>
        <p class="font-medium">Willem van der Maden</p>
        <p class="opacity-60">
          5/14/2025 · 1 min read
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <img 
      src="/square-workshop.png" 
      alt="DIS 2025 Workshop Banner (Image generated by Imagen 3, prompted by Willem van der Maden)" 
      class="apsect-video w-full rounded-xl mb-10" 
      width="800" 
      height="300" 
      loading="lazy" 
      decoding="async"
    />
    
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-a:text-blue-300 prose-a:underline-offset-4 prose-headings:mb-2 prose-p:text-[#b3b3b3]">
      <p>I'm excited to announce our Third Workshop on GenAI & Design Research, titled <strong>From Dead-Ends to Dialogue</strong>, as a companion to DIS '25 in Funchal, Portugal. The workshop dives into the "stopsigns"—those semantic and practical barriers that can impede thoughtful progress when integrating generative AI into design research.</p>
      
      <p>We invite you to participate by sharing concrete cases where you hit a conceptual, ethical, social, or pragmatic impasse with GenAI. Through group discussions and hands-on analysis, we'll collaboratively develop strategies to move beyond these obstacles and shape a robust research agenda.</p>
      
      <p>Check out the full details and submit your paper here: <a href="/DISworkshop2025">/DISworkshop2025</a>.</p>
      
      <p><strong>Key Dates:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Submission Deadline: <s>13th June 2025</s> <strong>23rd June 2025</strong><br/>
        <em>(Early submitters have already received an email. Extension open for a few more spots!)</em></li>
        <li>Notification of Acceptance: <s>20th June 2025</s> <strong>27th June 2025</strong></li>
        <li>Workshop Date: 6th July 2025 (during DIS '25, July 5–9, 2025)</li>
        <li>Note: For early bird registration requests, please contact us before June 3rd</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p>Looking forward to seeing you in Funchal!"</p>
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .aspect-square {
    aspect-ratio: 1/1;
  }
  
  .apsect-video {
    aspect-ratio: 16/9;
  }
  
  .w-\[40px\] {
    width: 40px;
  }
  
  .rounded-xl {
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
  }
  
  /* Prose styles */
  .prose {
    color: #e0e0e0;
  }
  
  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  
  .prose strong {
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  
  .prose a {
    color: #93c5fd;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 4px;
  }
  
  .prose ul {
    list-style-type: disc;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  
  .prose li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  
  .prose em {
    font-style: italic;
  }
  
  .prose s {
    text-decoration: line-through;
  }
  
  .prose-invert {
    color: #e0e0e0;
  }
  
  .prose-a\:text-blue-300 a {
    color: #93c5fd;
  }
  
  .prose-a\:underline-offset-4 a {
    text-underline-offset: 4px;
  }
  
  .prose-headings\:mb-2 h1,
  .prose-headings\:mb-2 h2,
  .prose-headings\:mb-2 h3,
  .prose-headings\:mb-2 h4,
  .prose-headings\:mb-2 h5,
  .prose-headings\:mb-2 h6 {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  
  .prose-p\:text-\[\#b3b3b3\] p {
    color: #b3b3b3;
  }
</style>